nt":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior text targets summarization correctness from given input data, which can be tested at the summarizer function/object boundary with fixed fixtures (MOCK-MISS=no). No explicit requirement for real HTTP/OS/subprocess (REAL-INFRA=no). Rejected Agentic because the behavior text does not state an AI/ML or LLM dependency; it only states accuracy against provided key values.","test_description":"Call the summary-generation function with fixed input containing clear key metrics/counts/deltas; assert the produced narrative includes and preserves those key values (no numeric drift, inversion, or omission).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.62,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly crosses real infrastructure boundary: end-to-end delivery to a recipient inbox requires real email transport/inbox interaction (REAL-INFRA=yes, MOCK-HIDE=yes). In-process mocks can validate wiring but can still miss deliverability/inbox placement failures. Rejected Workflow because no multiple agentic decisions are specified; this is end-to-end system integration, not multi-agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled run in an environment using real internal data endpoints (or realistic test instances) and a real test mailbox; assert one complete report email is received by the configured recipient, with expected subject/body and no pipeline abort.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is orchestration/state handoff: email failure triggers local persistence, then next run consumes persisted report and retries delivery (MOCK-MISS=yes). This can be reproduced with an in-process email adapter stub that raises unreachable errors plus real local filesystem in a temp directory; no real external network is strictly required for this behavior (REAL-INFRA demoted). Rejected System because behavior text focuses on fallback+retry semantics (`saved to a local file` and `retried on the next scheduled run`), which can be validated without real email infrastructure.","test_description":"Run 1: email adapter throws unreachable error; assert report is written to fallback file and marked pending. Run 2: email adapter succeeds; assert pending file is retried/sent, then cleared or marked delivered, with no duplicate new-generation side effects.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.35,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
